[2] Viet Nam: vaccine
Date: Wed 27 Aug 2008
Source: Thanh Nien (Young People) News [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/healthy/?catid=8&newsid=41515>


The Ministry of Health has approved the testing of a dengue fever vaccine
on locals in the southern province of An Giang. The ChimeriVax vaccine,
produced by international vaccine research and production company Sanofi
Pasteur, will undergo a 6 year trial to test its seroconversion rate
(ability to produce antibodies) against 4 dengue virus serotypes. The
safety of the drug will also be evaluated during the trial.

The Pasteur Institute of Ho Chi Minh City will conduct the trial on 180
healthy people of different ages in the province through 2014. Sanofi
Pasteur, the vaccine division of the France-based Sanofi-Aventis Group, has
already completed 2 trial phases of the tetravalent vaccine.

The latest test results were presented last September [2007] with a 100 per
cent seroconversion rate reported for all 4 dengue serotypes. [According to
a newswire from the Viet Nam news agency submitted by PRO/MBDS Rapporteur
Vern Weitzel "the vaccine has been tested by many countries with a
protection rate of between 83-100 per cent." - Mod.MPP] The 3rd trial phase
was launched this year [2008] in Latin America and Asia.

More than 28 890 dengue fever cases have been reported in Viet Nam this
year [2008], including 28 that have ended in death, according to the
Ministry of Health.

[byline: Nam Son]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[Given the difficulty in achieving and sustaining mosquito dengue virus
vectors population reduction through community-based breeding site
elimination, vaccines become an increasingly attractive approach to
reducing dengue cases. The challenge has been to develop a single effective
vaccine that elicits a good simultaneous immune response to all 4 dengue
virus serotypes, eliminating the risk of immune enhancement of virus
attachment. - Mod.TY

To date, there have been nearly 36 900 cases and 33 deaths of dengue
reported in Viet Nam during 2008, with more than 6100 cases from Ho Chi
Minh city. While the overall total of cases reported for the country this
year (2008) represents a 24 per cent decrease in reported cases when
compared with reported cases during the same period in 2007, this year has
had significant dengue activity when compared with earlier years. A total
of 3550 cases and 6 fatalities from dengue fever had been detected in Viet
Nam as of 27 Aug 2008 (see prior PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam (10)
20080731.2349).

According to the 2nd newswire, a 6-year vaccine trial of seroconversion
test against 4 serotypes of dengue virus will be conducted in An Giang
province. If the vaccine proves to be safe and effective, it will be a long
awaited tool to reduce the morbidity and mortality due to dengue virus
infection in the region, as it has been a major disease burden not only in
Viet Nam but also in other countries in the MBDS region.

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg>
and <http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=14.9,108.5,5>. This map shows other
outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries that have been reported on
ProMED-mail. The postings can be directly accessed through this map. -
Mods.YMA/MPP]

